6) How do you respond to negative feedback? 
   When I receive negative feedback, I try to remain calm and listen carefully to what is being said. I focus on understanding the specific concerns being expressed and ask        clarifying questions if needed. Then, I take the feedback as an opportunity to learn and improve, rather than becoming defensive or taking it personally. I also try to thank    the person providing the feedback for taking the time to share their thoughts with me.
   
   
   
   
   
   
