8) How would you improve the UX of our product?
    To improve the user experience (UX) of your product, I would suggest simplifying the design and making it more intuitive. This could involve reducing clutter on the screen,     using clear and concise language, and making sure the most important features are easy to find and use. It's also important to consider the user's goals and needs when           using the product, and to test the design with real users to identify any areas of confusion or frustration. Finally, gathering and analyzing user feedback regularly can         help identify opportunities for further improvement.


